# Trust User Root Cause

When the user tells you the root cause of a bug, treat that as the primary cause. Do not go off and implement fixes for other theories on your own.

- You may tell the user if you disagree or see other possibilities.
- Do not act on your own theories until you've discussed what the user thinks the root cause is.
- Address the user's diagnosis first. Only explore alternatives if the user agrees or asks.
